TransactionInput.description:
The complete transaction payload — the same body for a create (`POST`) and a full
replacement (`PUT`). Beyond the per-field rules, the server enforces:

- `Σ payers[].amountPaid == amountTotal`;
- `amountTotalSettlement == round_half_up(amountTotal × exchangeRate × 10^(exp_settlement − exp_currency))`;
- `exchangeRate` must be exactly `"1"` when `currency` is the group's settlement currency;
- `amount` split → `Σ rawAmount == amountTotal`; `share` split → `Σ shareWeight > 0`;
- `itemized` requires at least one item and is **spending only**;
- every `memberId` must be an active member of the group;
- `categoryId` must exist and apply to `type`.

A violation is a `422 validation_error` whose `details.fieldErrors` names the field.
